Class GymManager

java.lang.Object
models.GymManager
public class GymManager
extends java.lang.Object
The GymManager class is the user interface class that processes the command line inputs and prints the corresponding outputs.
Author:
Jackson Lee, Serena Zeng

      Returns:
      true if membership cancel success, false otherwise

    • handleCheckIn

      private boolean handleCheckIn​(java.lang.String command)
      Handles inputs with command C Parses command for fitness class and member information Checks in the member if 1. The member is in the database 2. Their membership is not expired, their 3. Their date of birth is valid 4. The specified class exists 5. The class has no time conflict with the member's other fitness clases 6. The member is not already checked in Displays appropriate error messages if unable to check in member to class
      Parameters:
      command - Entire line of instruction containing member and class information
      Returns:
      true if member checked in for class successfully, false otherwise

    • handleDropClass

      private boolean handleDropClass​(java.lang.String command)
      Handles inputs with command D Parses command for fitness class and member information Drops the member from the class if 1. The member is initially checked into the class 2. Their date of birth is valid 3. The specified class exists Displays appropriate error messages if unable to drop member from class
      Parameters:
      command - Entire line of instruction containing member and class information
      Returns:
      true if member dropped from class successfully, false otherwise
